9	/// This tool takes a snippet of CUDA-Q code, translates it to the Quake
10	/// dialect, runs user-specified passes, and prints the result. (Note that Quake
11	/// is a "minimalist" dialect, so translating to Quake can and does make use of
12	/// other MLIR dialects as well. These other dialects are convenient but not the
